00:01:58.820 --> 00:02:03.270
[Lover Merman — Only Nava]
♫ We don't have to tell anyone ♫

00:02:03.270 --> 00:02:06.450
[Previously]

00:02:06.450 --> 00:02:08.010
My name is Phurich.

00:02:08.010 --> 00:02:09.280
I'm Nava.

00:02:09.280 --> 00:02:12.610
This is Phurich,
my best friend from Bangkok.

00:02:12.610 --> 00:02:15.820
From now on,
Phurich will be working here with us.

00:02:15.820 --> 00:02:17.500
Phu is a real player.

00:02:17.500 --> 00:02:20.250
He flirts with everyone.
If you can, just avoid him.

00:02:20.250 --> 00:02:22.970
I don't want to see my little brother
get his heart broken.

00:02:22.970 --> 00:02:27.880
As for Phu, if he ever found out the truth, he wouldn't be able to handle it.

00:02:29.100 --> 00:02:30.940
Is there something you need?

00:02:30.940 --> 00:02:32.820
I'm supposed to start
my internship here tomorrow.

00:02:32.820 --> 00:02:35.050
An intern is starting at the bar tomorrow.

00:02:35.050 --> 00:02:37.630
He's all yours. I don't like training people.

00:02:37.630 --> 00:02:41.390
I'd advise you not to touch that.

00:02:41.390 --> 00:02:43.310
What kind of fish does this scale come from?

00:02:43.310 --> 00:02:48.040
If I told you it was a merman's scale, would you believe me?

00:02:48.040 --> 00:02:49.310
I'd have to be crazy to believe that.

00:02:49.310 --> 00:02:51.490
On the night before a full moon,

00:02:51.490 --> 00:02:55.600
an eight-pointed star is supposed to appear
on each of their bodies.

00:02:55.600 --> 00:02:59.870
If someone can show me a real, live merman, then I'll believe them.

00:02:59.870 --> 00:03:01.840
- Hey, Maiek.
- Yes?

00:03:01.840 --> 00:03:03.180
Close up the bar for me, will you?

00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:05.930
I'm going to take some customers out. Thanks.

00:03:05.930 --> 00:03:07.220
- No problem.
- And clear my glass for me.

00:03:07.220 --> 00:03:09.020
You got it.

00:04:10.150 --> 00:04:12.830
Hey, Nava. Are you heading back?

00:04:12.830 --> 00:04:14.930
I can give you a ride.

00:04:14.930 --> 00:04:18.260
Could I just sit here for a little longer?

00:04:18.260 --> 00:04:21.770
Okay, then. I'll wait for you on the shore.

00:04:21.770 --> 00:04:23.620
Okay.

00:04:23.620 --> 00:04:24.720
See you in a bit.

00:04:24.720 --> 00:04:26.280
Okay.

00:04:26.280 --> 00:04:27.880
I'm heading off.

00:04:46.780 --> 00:04:48.380
A merman?

00:04:54.240 --> 00:04:55.940
Phurich!

00:05:06.890 --> 00:05:09.250
I shouldn't have drunk so much.

00:05:11.080 --> 00:05:13.750
Ugh...

00:06:01.370 --> 00:06:03.720
How did I even get back here?

00:06:28.480 --> 00:06:30.790
I really shouldn't have drunk that much.

00:06:30.790 --> 00:06:33.470
This hangover is brutal.

00:06:33.470 --> 00:06:35.890
And I'm in a hurry, too.

00:06:53.830 --> 00:06:55.230
Hey!

00:07:12.840 --> 00:07:15.040
What a terrible start to the day.

00:07:17.530 --> 00:07:19.650
Should I call my insurance?

00:07:23.090 --> 00:07:27.450
I don't think that's the first thing
you should be saying to me.

00:07:27.450 --> 00:07:31.550
Look, I'm in a real hurry. I'm not looking for any trouble.

00:07:31.550 --> 00:07:33.424
I don't care if you're in a hurry.

00:07:33.424 --> 00:07:36.754
And I'm not looking for trouble
with your kind, either.

00:07:37.410 --> 00:07:40.600
"My kind?" What is that supposed to mean?

00:07:41.280 --> 00:07:43.210
The kind of person who makes a mistake
and doesn't apologize.

00:07:43.210 --> 00:07:45.880
What kind of person
do you think that makes you?

00:07:45.880 --> 00:07:47.380
Oh, really?

00:07:49.510 --> 00:07:50.720
Well, one thing's for sure.

00:07:50.720 --> 00:07:54.770
At least I'm not the one who starts
with snide remarks, unlike you.

00:08:09.590 --> 00:08:11.740
Look, about what happened with the car,
I'm sorry.

00:08:11.740 --> 00:08:13.940
I was driving carelessly.

00:08:16.670 --> 00:08:19.620
My car just has a little scratch. It's fine.

00:08:23.833 --> 00:08:27.572
Oh, and one more thing.

00:08:27.572 --> 00:08:29.580
Even if you did call your insurance,

00:08:29.580 --> 00:08:32.610
no agent would bother dragging themselves
all the way out here.

00:08:32.610 --> 00:08:36.096
Don't forget, this is an island, not Bangkok.

00:08:36.096 --> 00:08:38.696
The people here don't live like you do.

00:08:40.111 --> 00:08:41.911
Excuse me.

00:09:07.400 --> 00:09:09.300
Are you Nava?

00:09:09.300 --> 00:09:10.842
Yes. And you are?

00:09:10.842 --> 00:09:12.299
He's my younger brother, Ping.

00:09:12.299 --> 00:09:14.524
Phana asked us both to look after him.

00:09:14.524 --> 00:09:16.430
He'll be working behind the bar.

00:09:17.118 --> 00:09:18.718
Of course.

00:09:19.456 --> 00:09:21.200
If there's anything you need, just ask.

00:09:21.200 --> 00:09:23.200
Okay, thank you.

00:09:28.442 --> 00:09:31.128
Getting the bar's number one bartender
to show him the ropes.

00:09:31.128 --> 00:09:33.481
My brother is so lucky.

00:09:33.481 --> 00:09:35.100
Oh, Ping.

00:09:35.100 --> 00:09:37.998
Could you take the bottles out of that crate
and arrange them on the bar for me?

00:09:37.998 --> 00:09:39.749
I'll be right back.
I'm just going to the kitchen.

00:09:39.749 --> 00:09:41.649
You got it.

00:09:47.160 --> 00:09:49.370
So, Ping, are you from around here?

00:09:49.370 --> 00:09:51.950
Yes, but I went to the mainland for school.

00:09:51.950 --> 00:09:54.170
I only come back once in a while.

00:09:54.950 --> 00:09:58.380
Why do you ask? Do I not look like a local?

00:09:59.230 --> 00:10:02.020
I'm pretty sure we've never met before,

00:10:02.020 --> 00:10:05.340
but for some reason,
there's something familiar about you.

00:10:05.340 --> 00:10:08.960
Yeah, I feel the same way.

00:10:12.430 --> 00:10:14.970
You can put all the non-soda mixers in here.

00:10:14.970 --> 00:10:17.300
It makes them easier to grab for customers.

00:10:17.300 --> 00:10:20.770
Also, can you tell Timmy we need more whiskey
restocked at the front bar?

00:10:20.770 --> 00:10:22.470
You got it.

00:10:29.399 --> 00:10:31.020
Nava.

00:10:31.020 --> 00:10:32.293
Yes?

00:10:32.293 --> 00:10:33.920
Has Phana gotten in yet?

00:10:33.920 --> 00:10:36.250
He should have arrived by now.

00:10:43.350 --> 00:10:45.740
Are you hungover, Phurich?

00:10:46.980 --> 00:10:48.980
Are you worried about me?

00:10:50.750 --> 00:10:54.170
Anyone who saw the state you're in
would think the same thing.

00:10:58.260 --> 00:11:02.170
Then what do I have to do
to make you actually worry about me?

00:11:04.130 --> 00:11:06.520
And why would I need to worry about you?

00:11:08.800 --> 00:11:10.800
Because I like you.

00:11:15.150 --> 00:11:16.470
This is Ping.

00:11:16.470 --> 00:11:18.620
Phana hired him as an intern.

00:11:18.620 --> 00:11:20.710
- This is Phurich. He's--
- Are you Nava's boyfriend?

00:11:20.710 --> 00:11:22.600
- No.
- Yes.

00:11:24.629 --> 00:11:26.360
But I will be soon.

00:11:26.360 --> 00:11:29.650
This is Phurich, Phana's friend and a co-owner of the bar.

00:11:29.650 --> 00:11:32.070
My apologies, Phurich.

00:11:49.120 --> 00:11:51.380
You're in early today.

00:11:51.380 --> 00:11:54.243
Don't hit me. My head is already killing me.

00:11:54.243 --> 00:11:57.193
I had to do way too many shots
with customers last night.

00:11:57.875 --> 00:12:01.770
Here, you should have
the standard staff remedy for that.

00:12:01.770 --> 00:12:03.030
Nava.

00:12:03.030 --> 00:12:06.610
Could you get a hot honey lemon drink
for Phurich?

00:12:06.610 --> 00:12:08.280
Of course.

00:12:14.149 --> 00:12:15.949
Hey, Phana.

00:12:16.699 --> 00:12:19.129
Last night, I think...

00:12:21.008 --> 00:12:23.258
I saw something.

00:12:25.210 --> 00:12:27.370
It looked like a merman.

00:12:30.770 --> 00:12:32.570
Excuse me.

00:12:34.560 --> 00:12:36.470
What are you rambling about, Phu?

00:12:36.470 --> 00:12:39.100
There's no such thing as mermaids.

00:12:39.100 --> 00:12:41.340
That's what I thought, too.

00:12:41.340 --> 00:12:45.840
But I'm telling you,
my eyes weren't playing tricks on me.

00:12:47.710 --> 00:12:50.000
Where did you see it?

00:12:50.000 --> 00:12:51.700
Last night.

00:12:52.490 --> 00:12:55.470
After I left the customers,

00:12:55.470 --> 00:12:58.030
I went to sit by the beach.

00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:02.630
Even though I couldn't see it clearly,

00:13:02.630 --> 00:13:06.480
I'm confident that's what it was.

00:13:29.680 --> 00:13:31.180
A merman?

00:13:33.640 --> 00:13:38.420
But thinking back on it, it looked like...

00:13:55.920 --> 00:13:58.020
Looked like what?

00:13:59.090 --> 00:14:00.790
Like...

00:14:02.530 --> 00:14:04.090
Oh, Phurich.

00:14:04.090 --> 00:14:06.330
Sober now, are we?

00:14:09.468 --> 00:14:11.144
You shouldn't pass out drunk like that again.

00:14:11.144 --> 00:14:12.805
You're going to get sick.

00:14:12.805 --> 00:14:14.213
What are you talking about, Lek?

00:14:14.213 --> 00:14:17.143
Well, last night, I was on my way to meet a friend at the beach,

00:14:17.143 --> 00:14:21.080
and I happened to find Phurich
passed out drunk on the sand.

00:14:21.080 --> 00:14:23.020
Oh, Phu.

00:14:23.020 --> 00:14:27.500
Turns out you were just drunk
and dreaming that you saw a merman.

00:14:32.360 --> 00:14:34.232
Let me tell you something.

00:14:34.232 --> 00:14:36.089
This isn't Bangkok, you know.

00:14:36.089 --> 00:14:40.349
You can't just get wasted
and easily grab a taxi home.

00:14:40.349 --> 00:14:43.468
Even if the people on this island are harmless,

00:14:43.468 --> 00:14:47.350
it doesn't mean it's completely safe
for a newcomer like you.

00:14:48.570 --> 00:14:51.562
Yeah... I'm sorry.

00:14:51.562 --> 00:14:54.602
I'll take better care of myself from now on.

00:14:54.602 --> 00:14:56.545
Good.

00:14:56.545 --> 00:14:58.300
And thank you for last night, Lek.

00:14:58.300 --> 00:14:59.800
Of course.

00:15:11.820 --> 00:15:13.569
What Phu was talking about...

00:15:13.569 --> 00:15:15.280
was he talking about you, Nava?

00:15:15.280 --> 00:15:16.847
Um...

00:15:16.847 --> 00:15:19.240
You knew, Phana?

00:15:19.240 --> 00:15:21.860
It was pretty obvious.

00:15:21.860 --> 00:15:24.731
Yesterday, I swam a little too far
from the hidden beach.

00:15:24.731 --> 00:15:26.985
I didn't think anyone would see me.

00:15:38.190 --> 00:15:39.404
It's okay.

00:15:39.404 --> 00:15:41.760
But I don't want you to be careless, either.

00:15:41.760 --> 00:15:46.510
Nowadays, there aren't many people left
on the island who know about merfolk.

00:15:46.510 --> 00:15:49.470
And it's best if we keep it that way,

00:15:49.470 --> 00:15:52.190
for your own safety.

00:15:56.110 --> 00:15:58.750
I'll be more careful from now on.

00:16:00.160 --> 00:16:03.831
Speaking of which,
are you going to see Den today?

00:16:03.831 --> 00:16:05.656
I'm heading out now anyway.

00:16:05.656 --> 00:16:07.360
Do you want a ride?

00:16:07.360 --> 00:16:10.530
No, that's okay. I'd rather take my motorbike.

00:16:10.530 --> 00:16:13.040
That way, I can get back quickly
to prep the bar.

00:16:13.040 --> 00:16:14.590
Okay, then. I'm heading out.

00:16:14.590 --> 00:16:16.820
- Okay.
- Be safe.

00:16:39.020 --> 00:16:42.270
I was just about to head into town for a bit.

00:16:42.270 --> 00:16:44.384
Can I tag along?

00:16:45.279 --> 00:16:47.830
I'm just going to the barbershop. That's it.

00:16:47.830 --> 00:16:49.102
That's fine.

00:16:49.102 --> 00:16:51.550
I'll go to the barbershop with you.

00:16:52.833 --> 00:16:56.013
It would be more convenient for you
to take your own car.

00:17:00.270 --> 00:17:03.910
You don't pull any punches, do you?

00:17:09.880 --> 00:17:11.600
Let me ask you something directly.

00:17:11.600 --> 00:17:13.116
Everything you're doing...

00:17:13.116 --> 00:17:15.176
Are you hitting on me?

00:17:24.050 --> 00:17:25.711
Yes.

00:17:25.711 --> 00:17:27.860
I'm hitting on you.

00:17:30.190 --> 00:17:33.420
I apologize if I gave you the wrong impression
the other day.

00:17:33.420 --> 00:17:36.900
I honestly just thought you were a customer.

00:17:36.900 --> 00:17:39.980
I was just playing along
like any bartender would.

00:17:39.980 --> 00:17:43.190
I never meant to make you think
it was more than that.

00:17:43.190 --> 00:17:44.757
So what?

00:17:44.757 --> 00:17:47.040
I genuinely like you.

00:17:50.385 --> 00:17:52.895
And what is it about me that you like?

00:17:56.910 --> 00:17:58.896
Well...

00:17:58.896 --> 00:18:01.060
I don't really know.

00:18:01.060 --> 00:18:04.290
I just have this feeling
that if I let you get away,

00:18:04.290 --> 00:18:07.400
it would be the biggest regret of my life.

00:18:12.290 --> 00:18:14.990
In that case,
I'm tired of having this conversation with you.

00:18:25.618 --> 00:18:28.018
What is it now, Grandpa?

00:18:30.354 --> 00:18:32.884
Don't tell me you're out of gas.

00:18:38.830 --> 00:18:40.730
Do you need a ride?

00:18:42.350 --> 00:18:45.120
But aren't you in a hurry?

00:18:45.120 --> 00:18:47.180
You said you had to get to the bar.

00:18:47.180 --> 00:18:49.180
I am one of the owners now.

00:18:49.180 --> 00:18:52.690
And I'm very strict about employees being late.

00:19:00.560 --> 00:19:02.260
Fine.

00:19:06.750 --> 00:19:09.170
But could you please let go of my arm?

00:19:11.730 --> 00:19:13.230
Right.

00:19:19.143 --> 00:19:20.843
Lead the way.

00:20:15.260 --> 00:20:17.269
Um... I'm sorry.

00:20:17.269 --> 00:20:19.930
I didn't mean to be rude.

00:20:19.930 --> 00:20:22.200
I haven't said anything.

00:20:22.200 --> 00:20:23.966
Oh, right.

00:20:24.590 --> 00:20:27.640
So, how was your first day of work?

00:20:27.640 --> 00:20:28.710
It was good.

00:20:28.710 --> 00:20:32.040
Timmy and Nava taught me everything
step-by-step.

00:20:32.040 --> 00:20:36.330
For now, I'm just trying to get familiar
with where everything is.

00:20:36.330 --> 00:20:38.290
That's good.

00:20:38.290 --> 00:20:42.070
Just learn at your own pace.
If you get confused, just ask.

00:20:47.119 --> 00:20:49.909
Okay, thank you.

00:20:54.240 --> 00:20:56.765
Oh, Timmy, perfect timing.

00:20:56.765 --> 00:20:58.476
A Manhattan, as usual.

00:20:58.476 --> 00:21:00.346
When you're done,
just leave it for me over there.

00:21:00.346 --> 00:21:02.070
You got it.

00:21:06.450 --> 00:21:08.830
Does Phana normally drink at this time of day?

00:21:08.830 --> 00:21:11.670
"Normally?" Of course not.

00:21:11.670 --> 00:21:15.363
If he's drinking at this hour,
he definitely had a fight with Namhom.

00:21:15.363 --> 00:21:16.959
Namhom?

00:21:16.959 --> 00:21:19.357
Yeah, his girlfriend.

00:21:19.357 --> 00:21:21.703
They fight constantly.

00:21:21.703 --> 00:21:23.134
But he really loves her.

00:21:23.134 --> 00:21:26.486
I see them argue all the time, like twice a week,

00:21:26.486 --> 00:21:28.823
but they never actually break up.

00:21:31.840 --> 00:21:36.200
[Ferry Kohkhen]

00:21:38.920 --> 00:21:41.240
[Boat Ticket Sales]

00:21:44.160 --> 00:21:46.320
[Speedboat Port]

00:21:53.436 --> 00:21:55.816
Is this your usual barbershop?

00:21:55.816 --> 00:21:58.421
There are only a few on the island.

00:21:58.421 --> 00:22:00.579
Thanks for the ride.

00:22:03.740 --> 00:22:07.325
When you're done here,
feel free to call me anytime.

00:22:07.325 --> 00:22:09.919
I'll just walk around town while I wait.

00:22:09.919 --> 00:22:12.144
But I don't have your number.

00:22:13.334 --> 00:22:15.704
Are you asking for my number?

00:22:28.857 --> 00:22:32.995
Either way, I need your number, and you need to have mine.

00:22:51.288 --> 00:22:53.388
Don't forget to save it.

00:22:53.388 --> 00:22:55.868
You can call me anytime.

00:22:58.510 --> 00:23:00.510
Don't hesitate.

00:23:02.620 --> 00:23:05.130
I promise I won't be a bother.

00:23:13.700 --> 00:23:16.566
If you finish up,
you can head back on your own.

00:23:16.566 --> 00:23:18.390
You don't have to wait for me.

00:23:32.630 --> 00:23:35.660
There. What do you think?
I took the sides up a bit higher.

00:23:35.660 --> 00:23:36.860
Yeah.

00:23:36.860 --> 00:23:39.000
So, do you like it?

00:23:39.000 --> 00:23:42.150
Wow, Den. I love it.

00:23:43.520 --> 00:23:44.630
- That's quite a bit shorter.
- Yeah.

00:23:44.630 --> 00:23:45.610
Oh, hey, Nava.

00:23:45.610 --> 00:23:47.440
- Hello, Den.
- Hello.

00:23:47.440 --> 00:23:48.721
Oh, Phraphai.

00:23:48.721 --> 00:23:50.731
I didn't expect to see you here.

00:23:50.731 --> 00:23:52.403
Are you here for a haircut, too?

00:23:52.403 --> 00:23:54.075
Oh, no.

00:23:54.075 --> 00:23:56.750
Den asked me to order wine from the mainland,
so I just came to drop it off.

00:23:56.750 --> 00:23:58.280
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

00:23:58.280 --> 00:23:59.680
I actually ordered your wine, too,

00:23:59.680 --> 00:24:01.799
but I forgot to bring it.
